com.ebay.redlasersdk
Class BarcodeTypes

java.lang.Object
  com.ebay.redlasersdk.BarcodeTypes

public class BarcodeTypes
extends java.lang.Object

This class defines the barcode types that the RedLaser SDK can recognize, and contains methods for enabling and disabling each type. The hints member of the BarcodeScanActivity is a class of this type; enable or disable types in that object as appropriate to tell the SDK what barcode types to scan for.

getUpce

public boolean getUpce()
Gets whether UPC-E barcode type is enabled. UPC-E barcodes are 8 digits long and are different from the more common UPC-A type. UPC-A, in turn, has been deprecated and replaced by EAN-13.

Returns:
TRUE if UPC-E barcodes are enabled.

getEan8

public boolean getEan8()

Returns:
TRUE if EAN-8 barcodes are enabled

getEan13

public boolean getEan13()
Gets whether EAN13 barcode type is enabled. EAN-13 is a 13 digit fixed width barcode type that encodes GTIN-13 numbers. EAN-13 is a superset of UPC-A barcodes; to the scanner, every possible UPC-A barcode looks exactly like an EAN-13 barcode with a 0 as its first digit. This is why the SDK does not have a type for UPC-A barcodes; we consider all of them to be EAN-13 codes.

Returns:
TRUE if EAN-13 barcoes are enabled.

getSticky

public boolean getSticky()
Gets whether StickyBits barcode type is enabled.

Returns:
TRUE if StickyBits barcodes are enabled. The StickyBits type has been deprecated as of the 3.1 SDK. The SDK will no longer recognize StickyBits barcodes and this method always returns false.

setUpce

public void setUpce(boolean arg)
Enable or disable UPC-E barcode type. UPC-E barcodes are 8 digits long, and are different from the more common UPC-A barcode type. If you just want to enable 'UPC' barcodes, you most likely really want to enable the EAN-13 barcode type.

setEan8

public void setEan8(boolean arg)
Enable or disable EAN-8 barcode type.

setEan13

public void setEan13(boolean arg)
Enable or disable EAN-13 barcode type. EAN-13 barcodes are a superset of UPC-A barcodes. An EAN-13 barcode with a leading digit of 0 looks *exactly like* a UPC-A barcode. Since almost anyone using this family of barcodes needs to be able to handle GTIN-13 numbers, for simplicity the SDK always uses the EAN-13 type.

setRSS14

public void setRSS14(boolean arg)
Enable or disable RSS14 barcode type. The GS1 organization renamed RSS14 to GS1 Databar; this method and setGS1Databar() return the same value; that is, RSS14 and Databar are treated as the same barcode type.

setGS1Databar

public void setGS1Databar(boolean arg)
Enable or disable GS1 Databar barcode type. This includes GS1 Databar Omnidirectional, Truncated, Stacked, Stacked Omnidirectional, and Limited barcodes.

setGS1DatabarExpanded

public void setGS1DatabarExpanded(boolean arg)
Enable or disable GS1 Databar Expanded barcode type. Separate from the GS1 Databar type because the Expanded type returns a a fully qualified AI string (starting with the "]e0" symbology identifier prefix) whereas the Databar type returns a raw GTIN number.
